<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 10 at 5:23PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A band of snow will impact portions of southeastern Lewis and
Clark, Broadwater, west central Meagher, Jefferson and northwestern
Gallatin Counties through 615 PM MST...
At 521 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking a band of snow 12 miles
west of Helena, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Snow, heavy at times, will affect areas around Helena,
Boulder and Townsend through 615 PM. Visibility will fall
down to a quarter of a mile a times. If driving, be alert
for quickly changing road conditions.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
